post_cb({"34559542": {"ViewCount": "83", "Body": "<p>So the question is, does the latest standard specify when a function in the standard C++ library is declared inline or not? </p>\n<p>Looking at the <code>algorithm</code> header file from the Clang, GCC and MSVC implementations, every single function, except for the ones which are constexpr, are declared inline. </p>\n<p>I was gonna go on and ask about when to inline and what not, but I don't wanna have the usual argument about how the compiler knows better or micro optimizations, so I probably shouldn't even let this sentence stay in the question. Oh wait...</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "34559575", "Title": "Does the standard specify which functions are declared inline?", "CreationDate": "2016-01-01T19:57:54.563", "Id": "34559542", "CommentCount": "3", "FavoriteCount": "1", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2016-01-02T16:05:08.017", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "5212827", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><standards>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "34559575": {"Id": "34559575", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>No. The implementation author chooses.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_34559542_34559575_0\"><code>[C++14: 17.6.5.4/1]:</code> It is unspecified whether any global or non-member functions in the C++ standard library are defined as <code>inline</code> (7.1.2).</p>\n<p id=\"so_34559542_34559575_1\"><code>[C++14: 17.6.5.5/1]:</code> It is unspecified whether any member functions in the C++ standard library are defined as <code>inline</code> (7.1.2).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>And recall that this has nothing to do with actual inlining nowadays; it really only affects the ODR.</p>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "560648", "LastActivityDate": "2016-01-02T16:05:08.017", "Score": "9", "CreationDate": "2016-01-01T20:03:25.863", "ParentId": "34559542", "CommentCount": "2", "LastEditDate": "2016-01-02T16:05:08.017", "OwnerUserId": "560648"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_34559542_34559575_0": {"length": 8, "quality": 0.7272727272727273, "section_id": 6336}, "so_34559542_34559575_1": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.7, "section_id": 6340}}, "n3337": {"so_34559542_34559575_0": {"length": 8, "quality": 0.7272727272727273, "section_id": 6093}, "so_34559542_34559575_1": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.7, "section_id": 6097}}, "n4659": {"so_34559542_34559575_0": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.6363636363636364, "section_id": 7846}, "so_34559542_34559575_1": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.7, "section_id": 7850}}}});